      "stage_name": "Update Changelog",
      "completed_at": "2026-04-08T05:22:15.213245+00:00",
      "artifacts": {
        "changelog_entry": "[#368] T-IMG-019 CellposeSegment impl - replaces the flagship cellpose skeleton with a real setup/process/teardown block on the imaging E2E critical path. `CellposeSegment` now loads the model once per run via `setup()`, forwards `diameter` / `flow_threshold` / `cellprob_threshold` / `channels` into `state.eval(...)`, emits `Collection[Label]` with integer raster masks and populated `Label.Meta.n_objects`, and clears CUDA cache during teardown when a GPU-backed state was used. The imaging package test suite adds focused coverage for the friendly missing-dependency path, custom-model validation, parameter forwarding, label serialization, and collection behavior, and `tests/plugins/test_phase11_skeleton.py` gains `test_imaging_cellpose_impl_smoke()` so the workflow gate sees the concrete implementation. (@Codex, 2026-04-08, branch: feat/issue-368/T-IMG-019-cellpose-segment, session: 20260408-011132-phase-11-imaging-cellpose-chunk)"
      }
    }
